The paper discusses the implementation of preference handling and optimization in Answer Set Programming (ASP), which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the difficulty in implementing complex optimization criteria, which suggests that the paper may fall under the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) subcategory. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of meta-programming to develop a general implementation technique, which could fall under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) subcategory. The paper also mentions the use of dedicated modeling techniques, which could fall under the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) subcategory. Finally, the paper discusses the availability of complex preferences and optimization capacities for ASP applications, which could fall under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) subcategory.
